  "text": "In addition to the upstream control by hormones and growth factors, mTOR signaling is also regulated by amino acids and by cellular energy status. In most cell types, the effective amino acid is leucine (reviewed in Ref. [CITATION_1] . Omission of leucine from the medium causes the rapid inactivation of mTOR signaling, and 362 1548-9213/05 8.00 ©2006 Int. Union Physiol. Sci./Am. Physiol. Soc.",
